ISD lab sheet week 1                        26/09/2016
Questions:

1. What is a code repository (often also called version control system) used
for?
Code repository is a secure storage space used by companies 
2. Why is it advantageous to use a code repository? 
The greatest advantage to use a code repository, is it provides version control system a secure storage space to store large and sensitive data.
3. Describe the different “layers” of Software that exist on a typical
computer and explain why there are different layers of software.
There are 4 layers:
- User, input and output
- Application software
- System software 
- Hardware
 4. Describe what an algorithm is and explain why it is a useful “tool” to
translate from a human level problem (we can think of) to a computer
program.
An algorithm is a mathematical program used to run a computer program, it is highest level language used by humans to communicate 
